<!-- ABOUT THE PROJECT -->
## About The Project

[![Product Name Screen Shot][product-screenshot]](https://example.com)

This project contains the Frontend implementation of the Library Web Portal. This project is written using React library and Typescript.

Features Implemented
* User Authentication using Okta
* Stripe Payment 
* Payment Form created using custom layout React Component using Stripe Elements which are compliant to PCI DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard)

Jira Board: https://libraryportal.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/LIB/boards/4

<!-- GETTING STARTED -->
## Getting Started

You can either install the required software dependencies on your own machine or use Visual Studio Code IDE and DevContainers to setup the development environment.

### Prerequisites

This is an example of how to list things you need to use the software and how to install them.
* npm
  ```sh
  npm install npm@latest -g
  ```

### Installation

_Below is an example of how you can instruct your audience on installing and setting up your app. This template doesn't rely on any external dependencies or services._

1. Install prerequisite software before proceeding to Step 2
2. Clone the repo
   ```sh
   https://github.com/AngKokLeong/LibraryPortalFrontend.git
   ```
3. Type the linux command to change directory to LibraryPortalFrontend folder
   ```sh
    cd LibraryPortalFrontend
   ```
5. Install NPM packages
   ```sh
   npm install
   ```
6. Enter your API in `config.js`
   ```js
   const API_KEY = 'ENTER YOUR API';
   ```
